title: Man-Cave | Watch: The worst kick of the Rugby World Cup so far was also the best and here's why
text:
Between Ian Madigan's tears and everything else that was going on yesterday , it was easy to miss a moment from another match in the Rugby World Cup that held just as much emotion but for completely different reasons.
Namibia took an almighty thrashing in their final game of the tournament yesterday, losing to Argentina 64 -19, but they did so with good spirit as they let retiring prop Johnny Redelinghuys take an all-but pointless conversion in the 64th minute to send him off in style.
No he doesn't make it, but thanks to his Jonny Wilkinson impression and the gesture from his teammates, you can see it didn't matter and puts just as much of a smile on their faces as it would have done if it hadn't come up short.
Rugbyt's a great game now isn't it?
